<h2>Environment, Agriculture, Science & Technology</h2><p>
	<div id="column2_text" class="scrollable">
		<a href="http://www.fao.org/countryprofiles/default.asp?lang=en">FAO Country Profiles and Mapping Information System</a> - &quot;The FAO Country Profiles and Mapping Information System is a pioneering information retrieval tool which groups the organization's vast archive of information on its global activities in agriculture and development in a single area and catalogues it exclusively by country.&quot; <br>
        <a href="http://faostat.fao.org/">FAOSTAT Statistics Database</a> - Food and Agriculture Organization of the UN Contains  over 1 million time-series records covering international statistics on food production and aid, trade, land use and irrigation, forest and fishery products, population, agricultural machinery, and fertilizer and pesticides. <br>
        <a href="http://www.fas.usda.gov/">Foreign Agricultural Service</a> - Department of Agriculture site with statistical  reports and &quot;Hot Country Pages.&quot; <br>    
        <a href="http://www.st.nmfs.gov/st1/index.html">National Oceanic and Atmospheric Administration (NOAA) National Marine Fisheries Service</a> World Swordfish Study, World Shrimp and Salmon Culture, and World Fishing Fleets. <br>
        <a href="http://www.oecd.org/statisticsdata/0,3381,en_2649_37401_1_119656_1_1_37401,00.html">OECD Agriculture and Fisheries Statistics</a> - Includes detailed support estimates for both OECD and transition economies. <br>
        <a href="http://www.unece.org/trade/timber/mis/fp-stats.htm">UN/ECE Timber  Database</a> - Forest and Forest Industries Country Fact Sheets with overviews of forest resources and forest products in Europe, North America and the former  USSR. <br>
        <a href="http://www.ers.usda.gov/briefing/">USDA Economic Research Service Special Topic Briefing Rooms</a> - Department of Agriculture site with links to country and regional information, commodity market analysis, and other international agricultural data. <br>
        <a href="http://www.fas.usda.gov/commodities.asp">USDA Foreign Agricultural Service: Commodities and Products</a> - Links to US and international data. <br>
        <a href="http://usda.mannlib.cornell.edu/MannUsda/viewDocumentInfo.do?documentID=1194/">World Agricultural Supply and Demand Estimates (WASDE)</a> - Full-text monthly reports on the most current USDA forecasts of U.S. and world supply-use balances of major grains, soybeans and products, and cotton. <br>       
        <a href="http://www.ncdc.noaa.gov/ol/climate/climatedata.html">National Climatic Data Center Online Climate Data </a>- Climates of the World, Monthly Climatic  Data for the World, and Extreme Weather and Climate Events. <br>
        <a href="http://www.ciesin.org/">CIESIN: Center for International Earth Science Information Network</a> - Based at Columbia University, the site offers a wide range of data free of charge for personal and noncommercial use. <br>        
        <a href="http://www.oecd.org/statisticsdata/0,3381,en_2649_37465_1_119656_1_1_37465,00.html">OECD Environment Statistics</a> - Includes Key Environmental Indicators reports. <br>
        <a href="http://www.unep-wcmc.org/">UNEP-World Conservation Monitoring Centre</a> - Information on globally threatened animals and plants, including statistical analyses of global forest conservation, biodiversity profiles, natural capital indicators for OECD countries, and a protected areas database. <br>
        <a href="http://www.un.org/esa/agenda21/natlinfo/">United Nations Sustainable Development</a> - Natural resource, social, economic, and institutional indicators. <br>
        <a href="http://www.eia.doe.gov/emeu/international/contents.html">Energy Information Administration</a> - Information about Total Primary Energy, Petroleum, Natural Gas, Coal, Electricity, and Carbon Dioxide Emissions. Data may be searched by individual country. <br>
        <a href="http://www.iea.org/Textbase/stats/index.asp">International Energy Administration (IEA) </a> - Includes the  &quot;Monthly Electricity Survey,&quot; &quot;Monthly Price Statistics,&quot; &quot;Monthly Natural Gas Survey,&quot; &quot;Monthly Oil Survey,&quot; &quot;The World's Energy in Charts and Graphs,&quot; and &quot;IEA Energy Technology R&amp;D Statistics. <br>
        <a href="http://unstats.un.org/unsd/jodi/DataViewRecord.aspx">Joint Oil Data Initiative (JODI): Project on Monthly Oil Statistics</a> - Monthly data for the  biggest oil producing and consuming countries. **Under development.** <br>
        <a href="http://www.oecd-ilibrary.org/energy/data/iea-world-energy-statistics-and-balances_enestats-data-en">OECD Energy Statistics</a> - Energy statistics, prices and taxes and balances, nuclear electricity generation, CO2 emissions, natural, gas, coal, electricity  and renewables information. <br>
        <a href="http://www.nsf.gov/sbe/srs/intres/start.htm">National Science Foundation Science and Engineering Statistics</a> - Full-text publications on international resources for science and technology. <br>
        <a href="http://www.oecd.org/statisticsdata/0,3381,en_2649_37441_1_119656_1_1_37441,00.html">OECD Information and Communication Technologies Statistics</a> - Includes the Future of the Internet Economy, broadband statistics, and the OECD Communication Outlook. <br>
        <a href="http://www.bts.gov/programs/international/">Bureau of Transportation Statistics</a> - International transportation statistics including Latin American Transportation Fact Sheets, International Air Passenger and Freight Statistics, and International Travel and Tourism Statistics. <br>
        <a href="http://www.oecd.org/statisticsdata/0,3381,en_2649_34337_1_119656_1_1_1,00.html">OECD Transport Statistics</a> - International Road Traffic and Accident Database, International Transport Research Documentation, and Maritime Transport data.</div>
